# ZenUI - Glassmorphic Components Guide
## Critical Priority Implementation

---

## 1. Why Glassmorphic First?

Glassmorphic components are our **KEY DIFFERENTIATOR**. They are:
- Visually stunning and instantly recognizable
- Not commonly available in other libraries
- Perfect for showcasing our design quality
- Highly shareable on social media (X, LinkedIn, etc.)

---

## 2. Design Tokens for Glassmorphism

```css
/* packages/core/src/styles/glass-tokens.css */

:root {
  /* Glass Blur Levels */
  --glass-blur-sm: 8px;
  --glass-blur-md: 12px;
  --glass-blur-lg: 16px;
  --glass-blur-xl: 24px;
  
  /* Glass Backgrounds - Light Mode */
  --glass-bg-light: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  --glass-bg-light-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);
  --glass-bg-light-active: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.9);
  
  /* Glass Backgrounds - Dark Mode */
  --glass-bg-dark: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
  --glass-bg-dark-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
  --glass-bg-dark-active: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  
  /* Glass Borders */
  --glass-border-light: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  --glass-border-dark: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  --glass-border-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
  
  /* Glass Shadows - Multi-layer for depth */
  --glass-shadow-sm: 
    0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1),
    0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  --glass-shadow-md: 
    0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12),
    0 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  --glass-shadow-lg: 
    0 8px 32px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15),
    0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
  --glass-shadow-xl: 
    0 16px 48px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2),
    0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  
  /* Transition Timing */
  --glass-transition: 200ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  --glass-transition-slow: 300ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}
```

